WEBVTT

00:06.441 --> 00:07.877
- Previously on "Happy!"...

00:07.920 --> 00:09.052
- I would love to know

00:09.096 --> 00:10.488
what you and Sonny
had to talk about.

00:10.532 --> 00:11.837
- He's got blackmail
on everyone.

00:11.881 --> 00:13.361
It's on videotape.

00:13.404 --> 00:15.537
- The people on these tapes
protect him.

00:15.580 --> 00:17.365
- Kap, what do you think?

00:17.408 --> 00:19.236
- [screaming]

00:19.280 --> 00:21.499
- I think
it's fuckin' brilliant.

00:21.543 --> 00:24.198
- Holy guacamole,
it's Dayglo Doug!

00:24.241 --> 00:26.417
Dayglo Doug was there
when Sonny started.

00:26.461 --> 00:28.158
- Now you'll have
plenty of time

00:28.202 --> 00:30.552
to devote to your...passions.

00:30.595 --> 00:31.727
- Sounds like
a slam dunk witness

00:31.770 --> 00:33.207
to build the foundation
of your case on.

00:33.250 --> 00:35.165
- You were big, Doug.

00:35.209 --> 00:38.081
- Sonny just took
whatever he wanted to,

00:38.125 --> 00:39.822
starting with my show.

00:39.865 --> 00:42.651
- Hailey, I am so, so sorry.

00:42.694 --> 00:44.000
- Get away from me.

00:44.044 --> 00:46.350
- Listen, I've been
protecting you, haven't I?

00:47.438 --> 00:48.396
- [yelps]

00:48.439 --> 00:49.788
- You almost got hurt
back there.

00:49.832 --> 00:51.138
- It's like you're
two different people.

00:51.181 --> 00:53.227
- I'm Blue Scaramucci.

00:53.270 --> 00:55.533
I am trapped in you.

00:55.577 --> 00:58.884
My name is Orcus.

00:58.928 --> 01:00.103
- The Wishees.

01:00.147 --> 01:01.496
[gunshots]
- I killed it.

01:01.539 --> 01:03.237
Whatever it was that
came out of that thing,

01:03.280 --> 01:04.455
I put it in a jelly jar.

01:04.499 --> 01:06.762
- For now, I'm gonna
get this jelly open.

01:06.805 --> 01:08.111
[groans]

01:08.155 --> 01:09.895
[farting, liquid gurgling]

01:09.939 --> 01:10.896
[grunts]

01:10.940 --> 01:12.637
- Sax!

01:31.700 --> 01:34.746
- [groaning weakly]

01:39.273 --> 01:42.885
[sobbing]
No! No!

01:42.928 --> 01:45.322
Oh, oh.

01:47.324 --> 01:49.500
[water running]

01:54.201 --> 01:55.898
- Holy...
[bell dings]

02:23.491 --> 02:24.970
[bell dings]

02:41.248 --> 02:44.903
[cheerful music]

02:44.947 --> 02:47.297
- Closest thing
I have to hard evidence

02:47.341 --> 02:48.516
literally down the shitter.

02:48.559 --> 02:49.647
God damn it, Sax.

02:49.691 --> 02:51.693
- Yeah, it's probably
just as well.

02:51.736 --> 02:54.435
That palooka was a few bananas
short of a split.

02:54.478 --> 02:56.350
- He was right about one thing:

02:56.393 --> 02:59.962
those were the wrong tapes
at Sonny's place.

03:00.005 --> 03:01.616
The real stuff's gotta
be at Shine Tower,

03:01.659 --> 03:03.705
so that is where
we're gonna go.

03:03.748 --> 03:06.534
- Uh, hey, wait,
hold on. Hold on.

03:06.577 --> 03:08.753
I--I know I offered to help,
Policewoman,

03:08.797 --> 03:10.494
but go to Shine Tower?

03:10.538 --> 03:12.670
I might as well
pop a cyanide capsule

03:12.714 --> 03:14.498
and chase it with a Luger.

03:14.542 --> 03:16.587
- Oh, I could take you back to
Alpine Memories, if you prefer.

03:16.631 --> 03:19.242
- [laughs]

03:19.286 --> 03:20.765
You're not joking.

03:21.897 --> 03:23.551
Oh.

03:23.594 --> 03:25.944
Okay, uh, listen,
sweet cheeks,

03:25.988 --> 03:28.730
I've come up
with a better solution,

03:28.773 --> 03:33.256
one that I think would
work well for both of us:

03:33.300 --> 03:35.911
Brazil!

03:35.954 --> 03:40.524
You can relax on the beach,
work on your tan.

03:40.568 --> 03:44.876
I will whip up
a fresh new act.

03:44.920 --> 03:46.878
- You keep doing that, I'm
gonna shoot you in your face.

03:46.922 --> 03:48.315
- Yep.

03:48.358 --> 03:49.968
- Look.

03:50.012 --> 03:52.928
This was taken at a public
appearance nine days ago.

03:52.971 --> 03:55.278
I count four
of these furry fucks.

03:55.322 --> 03:57.454
If I emptied a gun
into one of them,

03:57.498 --> 03:58.760
who the hell is in that suit?

03:58.803 --> 03:59.891
- I'll get out of your hair.

03:59.935 --> 04:01.676
Just lend me a few bucks
for bus fare.

04:01.719 --> 04:03.765
I've always wanted
to see Schenectady.

04:03.808 --> 04:07.856
You'll never have to worry
about old Doug again.

04:07.899 --> 04:09.031
- This is your tape, Doug...

04:09.074 --> 04:10.946
- W--
- The one Sonny made.

04:10.989 --> 04:12.600
You don't have to be
afraid of him.

04:12.643 --> 04:14.950
He doesn't have anything
on you anymore.

04:14.993 --> 04:17.996
I'm going to Shine Tower.

04:18.040 --> 04:19.650
I could really use your help.

04:23.611 --> 04:25.395
- [sniffing]

04:25.439 --> 04:27.528
Nick!
Nick!

04:27.571 --> 04:28.964
[sniffing]

04:29.007 --> 04:30.705
Oh, come on, Nick,
where are you?

04:30.748 --> 04:32.794
Ooh!

04:32.837 --> 04:36.319
Oh, you cakes,
you yummy cakes!

04:36.363 --> 04:38.103
That reminds me of when
Amanda brought home

04:38.147 --> 04:40.758
that awful gluten-free cake
with the edible candles.

04:40.802 --> 04:42.499
And thatreminds me
of when Hailey

04:42.543 --> 04:44.501
burned a hole
in her Daisybots bedsheets.

04:44.545 --> 04:47.330
And thatreminds me of when Sax
tied sheets around his neck

04:47.374 --> 04:48.679
and told me to get
into my safe space

04:48.723 --> 04:50.115
because he wanted quiet time.

04:50.159 --> 04:51.813
And thatreminds me
of when Hailey

04:51.856 --> 04:54.555
got that pink singing
alarm clock for her--

04:54.598 --> 04:57.471
[gasps]
It's Hailey's birthday!

04:57.514 --> 05:01.953
[ragga jungle music]

05:01.997 --> 05:02.998
[spirited orchestral music]

05:03.041 --> 05:04.956
[speed metal music]

05:05.000 --> 05:06.958
[upbeat disco music]

05:07.002 --> 05:10.048
[elephant trumpets]

05:10.788 --> 05:14.052
[elephant trumpeting continues]

05:18.970 --> 05:21.843
[tires squeal]

05:21.886 --> 05:22.887
- Get in.

05:22.931 --> 05:24.019
- Sorry, fellas,
Janet warned me

05:24.062 --> 05:25.760
about getting into cars
with strangers

05:25.803 --> 05:28.371
without a bag of chaw
and a fresh pair of pantyhose.

05:28.415 --> 05:29.807
- Now, bitch.
Clock's ticking.

05:29.851 --> 05:32.810
[sinister music]

05:32.854 --> 05:34.377
♪

05:34.421 --> 05:36.553
[tires squeal]

05:36.597 --> 05:40.514
- All right, Sax,
get your shit together.

05:40.557 --> 05:41.950
You got a job to finish.

05:41.993 --> 05:43.038
- You know, if we're already

05:43.081 --> 05:45.170
gonna be doing
the last name thing,

05:45.214 --> 05:48.130
I just think introductions
would be proper.

05:48.173 --> 05:51.133
[eerie music]

05:51.176 --> 05:57.705
♪

05:57.748 --> 05:59.576
[laughs]

05:59.620 --> 06:03.406
Well, well, if it ain't
Humpty, Dumpty, and...

06:03.450 --> 06:04.407
what's your name again?

06:04.451 --> 06:06.017
- I ain't no Easter egg, Sax.

06:06.061 --> 06:07.410
- Well, you are dyed.

06:07.454 --> 06:10.979
[laughs]

06:11.022 --> 06:12.328
Get it?

06:12.372 --> 06:14.852
- Maybe you're feeling
a tiny smidgen of guilt

06:14.896 --> 06:16.114
for what you did to us...

06:16.158 --> 06:17.115
[gunshots]

06:17.159 --> 06:18.203
- [screaming]

06:18.247 --> 06:19.901
- And you're lashing out.

06:19.944 --> 06:21.206
- The only thing I'm feeling

06:21.250 --> 06:23.992
is a burning sensation
in my asshole,

06:24.035 --> 06:26.647
a gag reflex
from the combined stench

06:26.690 --> 06:28.953
of the four of us
in close quarters,

06:28.997 --> 06:31.216
the acute tedium
of this conversation,

06:31.260 --> 06:33.131
and a burning sensation
in my asshole.

06:33.175 --> 06:34.132
- You said that twice.

06:34.176 --> 06:36.831
- What I am not feeling

06:36.874 --> 06:40.051
is one shred of guilt for
having ventilated you dotards.

06:40.095 --> 06:43.141
In fact, if I had the chance
to do it again...

06:43.185 --> 06:44.926
wait, does that mean
I get to do it again?

06:44.969 --> 06:46.493
[gun hammers click]

06:46.536 --> 06:47.494
- Come on, Sax.

06:47.537 --> 06:48.582
Don't change the subject.

06:48.625 --> 06:49.844
- You know what you gotta do.

06:49.887 --> 06:53.151
- Spoiler: it involves bullets.

07:01.116 --> 07:04.075
[mysterious music]

07:04.119 --> 07:08.776
♪

07:08.819 --> 07:12.475
- Sorry to disappoint
you guys, but...

07:12.519 --> 07:14.042
I'm indisposed.

07:14.085 --> 07:15.957
I got this really important
thing I gotta take care of,

07:16.000 --> 07:17.828
so if you would just
let me out of this van.

07:17.872 --> 07:19.917
- Really?
And what exactly is that?

07:19.961 --> 07:21.528
- You can't remember, can you?

07:21.571 --> 07:23.486
- Um...

07:25.749 --> 07:27.577
Well, if I could,
why would I tell you?

07:27.621 --> 07:28.622
- Some dad.

07:28.665 --> 07:30.188
He forgot
his daughter's birthday.

07:30.232 --> 07:33.278
- Wait.
That today?

07:33.322 --> 07:34.671
I knew that.

07:34.715 --> 07:36.151
- And you need
to get her a present.

07:37.587 --> 07:40.503
- You know how long
it took me to find a Wishee?

07:40.547 --> 07:42.723
- Driver, take me to the place
that sells

07:42.766 --> 07:45.639
shit that kids like!

07:45.682 --> 07:48.163
- You're a killer, Sax,
a death dealer.

07:48.206 --> 07:49.207
- Ain't we the proof?

07:49.251 --> 07:50.818
- That's what you do good.

07:50.861 --> 07:52.602
You want to get your kid
a present, huh?

07:52.646 --> 07:54.517
Why don't you bring her
the head of you-know-who

07:54.561 --> 07:55.910
with a pretty bow on top?

07:55.953 --> 07:57.128
- I'm done with that.

07:57.172 --> 07:58.565
Listen, don't threaten me
with a good time.

07:58.608 --> 07:59.870
Besides, I'm retired
from that game.

07:59.914 --> 08:01.655
I got the watch to prove it
and everything.

08:01.698 --> 08:05.136
- Looks like you got
a retarded watch.

08:05.180 --> 08:07.225
- You can say you're retired
all you want.

08:07.269 --> 08:09.010
A tiger doesn't
just wake up one day

08:09.053 --> 08:10.707
and decide it's a canary.

08:10.751 --> 08:12.013
- No, it does not.

08:12.056 --> 08:13.928
- We'll make this simple.

08:13.971 --> 08:16.539
Either you're the one
taking the envelope,

08:16.583 --> 08:19.020
or you might just
find yourself inside of one.

08:19.063 --> 08:22.676
- I had you assholes all wrong.

08:22.719 --> 08:28.246
I thought you was hard-boiled,
but look at you...

08:28.290 --> 08:30.597
extra runny.

08:30.640 --> 08:33.600
[laughs]

08:35.645 --> 08:37.691
Extra runny.

08:39.606 --> 08:40.694
[smacking and thudding]

08:40.737 --> 08:41.695
[tires squeal]

08:41.738 --> 08:43.566
- Get off the bus, you moron!

08:43.610 --> 08:44.872
- Oof.
- Get some pants on!

08:44.915 --> 08:46.917
- [groans]

08:48.789 --> 08:50.617
Ah!

08:56.100 --> 08:57.711
- What do you want?

08:57.754 --> 08:59.713
- Is it cool
if we sit with you?

08:59.756 --> 09:04.108
- Shouldn't you be hanging out
with your queen bee, Dagny?

09:04.935 --> 09:06.023
- [slurping]

09:06.067 --> 09:08.852
- That's not really
a thing anymore.

09:10.637 --> 09:12.813
- So who was that old guy
at the zoo?

09:14.118 --> 09:15.598
- My boyfriend.

09:16.773 --> 09:17.774
- Cool.

09:18.862 --> 09:21.125
- I know you probably
hate us, but...

09:21.169 --> 09:23.737
- We're sorry
for being total dicks.

09:25.652 --> 09:26.696
Tastes like cake batter.

09:26.740 --> 09:29.699
- Well, it is my birthday.

09:29.743 --> 09:31.962
- Oh, my God,
it's your birthday?

09:32.006 --> 09:33.094
Happy birthday.

09:33.137 --> 09:36.053
You're totes JUULing with us.

10:01.949 --> 10:04.647
[dance music fades in]

10:04.691 --> 10:05.779
[canister hissing]

10:05.822 --> 10:07.824
[dance music]

10:07.868 --> 10:11.132
♪

10:11.175 --> 10:14.222
- [panting]

10:25.146 --> 10:28.105
[dance music]

10:28.149 --> 10:29.977
♪

10:30.020 --> 10:33.067
[panting]

10:35.852 --> 10:37.027
[canister hisses]

10:37.811 --> 10:39.203
[canister hisses, squeaks]

10:39.247 --> 10:40.291
[canister rattles]

10:40.335 --> 10:41.423
[canister hisses feebly]

10:41.466 --> 10:44.687
[panting]

10:48.996 --> 10:52.086
- What do we have in common?

10:52.129 --> 10:54.436
Not race.

10:54.479 --> 10:56.699
Not creed.

10:56.743 --> 10:58.440
Not religion.

10:58.483 --> 11:01.138
Certainly not
sexual orientation,

11:01.182 --> 11:03.706
whatever that might mean
around here.

11:03.750 --> 11:09.712
Not even possession
of two balls and two eyes.

11:09.756 --> 11:12.193
Hello, Trotsky.

11:12.236 --> 11:14.282
Looking good there.

11:14.325 --> 11:18.112
No, there's only one thing
that we have in common:

11:18.155 --> 11:20.201
death.

11:23.073 --> 11:28.905
Death, the fearof it, yes,
but also the lustfor it!

11:31.429 --> 11:34.998
All of us here
have taken lives.

11:35.042 --> 11:39.916
We have conjured death,
and now death waits upon us

11:39.960 --> 11:43.224
and death waits for us
impatiently.

11:43.267 --> 11:48.229
That is the thing we share.

11:48.272 --> 11:53.756
Black, white, brown,
it unitesus

11:53.800 --> 11:57.151
into a perfect brotherhood.

11:57.194 --> 11:59.066
Now, you take Odipo here.

11:59.109 --> 12:02.069
Odipo dismembered his wife
and his cousin

12:02.112 --> 12:05.768
when he found them making
the beast with two backs.

12:05.812 --> 12:08.902
His wife broke
the vows of marriage.

12:08.945 --> 12:12.427
His cousin broke
the covenant of family,

12:12.470 --> 12:14.777
such a messy business,

12:14.821 --> 12:17.519
such Sturm und Drang!

12:20.391 --> 12:24.874
But what Odipo gave to them
was simple, was pure,

12:24.918 --> 12:27.094
was perfection,

12:27.137 --> 12:30.837
and someday,
maybe someday soon,

12:30.880 --> 12:35.102
Odipo will join them in--
[farts]

12:40.629 --> 12:42.152
- Preach, brother.

12:51.509 --> 12:53.685
- Excuse me, please.

12:57.515 --> 13:00.997
[bluesy music]

13:07.525 --> 13:09.005
[device beeps melodically]

13:09.049 --> 13:10.964
[musical beat]

13:11.007 --> 13:12.313
[gun hammer clicks]

13:12.356 --> 13:14.184
- Take off your goddamn head.

13:16.056 --> 13:17.622
- Please don't shoot me.
- Shut up.

13:17.666 --> 13:19.015
- It looks human.

13:19.059 --> 13:20.756
- [screams]
Ow!

13:20.800 --> 13:21.844
- Name.

13:21.888 --> 13:23.846
- J-Jessup, J-Jessup Miller.

13:23.890 --> 13:26.544
- Jesus Christ,
it is, isn't it?

13:26.588 --> 13:27.850
How long have you worked
for Sonny Shine?

13:27.894 --> 13:30.070
- Since about six weeks back.

13:30.113 --> 13:32.681
- Right around when
I killed it. Times out.

13:32.724 --> 13:34.465
- Killed?
What do you mean, killed?

13:34.509 --> 13:36.424
- Tell me about the others.
You met them?

13:36.467 --> 13:37.904
- I--I--I mean, I work
with them every day,

13:37.947 --> 13:39.601
but I never properly
met any of 'em.

13:39.644 --> 13:41.690
High on their own farts,
those ones.

13:41.733 --> 13:42.691
I can't say I blame them.

13:42.734 --> 13:44.562
I mean, they is superstars.

13:44.606 --> 13:47.391
Still, I ain't ever even seen
anyone with their heads off.

13:47.435 --> 13:48.566
I'm just the new guy.

13:48.610 --> 13:49.916
I tried to get in good.

13:49.959 --> 13:52.701
I brought doughnuts,
Frappuccinos,

13:52.744 --> 13:54.659
even offered Mr. Shine
a blowie.

13:55.922 --> 13:57.749
That's how to move up
in this business.

13:57.793 --> 13:59.447
- Stop.

14:00.927 --> 14:02.537
You blew Sonny Shine?

14:02.580 --> 14:04.974
- No, ma'am.
He turned me down.

14:05.018 --> 14:06.758
But I think that rubbed
some of the other Wishees

14:06.802 --> 14:07.803
the wrong way.

14:07.847 --> 14:09.892
They're hella possessive
of Sonny,

14:09.936 --> 14:13.591
follow him around 24/7
always in character.

14:13.635 --> 14:15.593
- They got dressing rooms
like this one?

14:15.637 --> 14:17.073
- Not that I ever saw.

14:17.117 --> 14:18.945
They pretty much go
wherever they want around here,

14:18.988 --> 14:20.642
got the run of the place.

14:20.685 --> 14:23.950
Listen, old-timer,
I'm a team player.

14:23.993 --> 14:26.474
Maybe I give you a quick
blowie, y'all let me go.

14:26.517 --> 14:27.736
- Shut up!

14:27.779 --> 14:29.694
You watch him.

14:32.741 --> 14:34.874
I got an idea.

14:40.096 --> 14:42.011
- Pink.

14:42.055 --> 14:45.449
- At least we know
who one of us is.

14:45.493 --> 14:47.887
- You're right.
That--

14:47.930 --> 14:49.714
you're right.
This can't go on.

14:49.758 --> 14:51.107
- Really?

14:51.151 --> 14:53.153
Seems like things are
going pretty good for you.

14:53.196 --> 14:55.068
Nobody's trying
to whack you anymore.

14:55.111 --> 14:56.896
You got a bunch
of new friends.

14:56.939 --> 14:59.768
They all worship you like
you're some kind of God, Blue,

14:59.811 --> 15:02.466
like some kind of David Koresh
or Tony Robbins.

15:02.510 --> 15:05.948
- Screw those--

15:05.992 --> 15:09.169
screw those idiots.

15:09.212 --> 15:13.173
It's not me, Pink.
You know that.

15:13.216 --> 15:16.567
It's someone else.

15:16.611 --> 15:18.961
The thing is,

15:19.005 --> 15:23.966
there's less and less
of me every day.

15:24.010 --> 15:27.491
And I can't control that.

15:27.535 --> 15:32.192
And that's why--

15:32.235 --> 15:34.063
that's why I have to die.

15:34.107 --> 15:35.151
- Don't be so dramatic.

15:35.195 --> 15:37.153
- No, no, listen to me.

15:37.197 --> 15:40.809
I'm never getting out
of this thing alive.

15:40.852 --> 15:43.855
You got to think of it
like I'm already dead.

15:43.899 --> 15:46.075
The moment that Mikey
whispered in my ear,

15:46.119 --> 15:48.730
he gave me a death sentence.

15:51.037 --> 15:54.170
But...

15:54.214 --> 15:55.824
I can still fuck him.

15:55.867 --> 15:57.043
- Mikey?

15:57.086 --> 15:59.306
- No, Orcus.

15:59.349 --> 16:00.785
- I don't understand.

16:00.829 --> 16:05.616
- If I die, he dies.

16:07.575 --> 16:10.056
Either that
or he's trapped forever

16:10.099 --> 16:13.668
in some kind of
mindless flesh prison.

16:13.711 --> 16:14.843
I don't know.

16:14.886 --> 16:17.846
Either way, it is
all the way up his ass.

16:17.889 --> 16:23.112
- So let me get this right:
you want me to kill you, Blue.

16:23.156 --> 16:24.984
Is that right?

16:26.942 --> 16:28.813
- Yeah.

16:28.857 --> 16:29.814
- I can't do that.

16:29.858 --> 16:31.033
- Oh, Pink, come on.

16:31.077 --> 16:34.602
You're the only one that can.

16:34.645 --> 16:37.126
They all worship
the motherfuck.

16:37.170 --> 16:38.780
I can't do it myself.

16:38.823 --> 16:40.564
He'll just stop me.

16:40.608 --> 16:41.739
Please.

16:41.783 --> 16:44.699
If you love me,

16:44.742 --> 16:46.092
and I think you do,

16:46.135 --> 16:47.963
just end this.

16:48.007 --> 16:49.965
I'm begging you.

16:50.009 --> 16:51.923
- [crying]
Jesus, Blue, now?

16:51.967 --> 16:54.230
- No, no.

16:54.274 --> 16:55.797
I don't want
to see it coming.

16:55.840 --> 16:58.104
You gotta get me
when I least expect it.

17:02.673 --> 17:05.328
- I can't believe
this is even real.

17:06.808 --> 17:08.984
- How the hell
do you think I feel?

17:13.206 --> 17:16.644
- Hailey!
Hailey, I didn't forget!

17:16.687 --> 17:19.603
[sniffing]

17:19.647 --> 17:20.778
Oh, it's a cake.

17:20.822 --> 17:21.997
- Then He changed water
into wine.

17:22.041 --> 17:24.260
- I have a birthday cake
for a Hailey Hansen.

17:24.304 --> 17:26.001
- [blows noisemaker]

17:26.045 --> 17:27.959
- Says, "Love from the Squad."

17:28.003 --> 17:29.831
[together]
Happy birthday, Hailey.

17:29.874 --> 17:31.093
- Really?

17:31.137 --> 17:33.226
- Everyone deserves cake
on their birthday.

17:33.269 --> 17:36.620
- Okay, kids, let's sing
"Happy Birthday" to Hailey.

17:36.664 --> 17:41.930
all: ♪ Happy birthday to you

17:41.973 --> 17:47.240
♪ Happy birthday to you

17:47.283 --> 17:48.632
- ♪ Happy birthday to you

17:48.676 --> 17:50.330
all: ♪ Happy birthday,
dear Hailey ♪

17:50.373 --> 17:53.289
- ♪ Happy birthday to you

17:53.333 --> 17:54.812
♪ Happy birthday, dear Hailey

17:54.856 --> 17:55.987
all: ♪ Happy birthday to you

17:56.031 --> 17:57.076
- [gasps]

17:57.119 --> 17:58.816
[singing fades]

17:58.860 --> 18:01.819
["Hark!
The Herald Angels Sing"]

18:01.863 --> 18:05.127
♪

18:05.171 --> 18:07.651
- [giggles]

18:07.695 --> 18:09.392
- You think this is funny?

18:09.436 --> 18:11.873
- Hailey's got
a doodie cake!

18:11.916 --> 18:13.744
[laughter]
- Girls!

18:13.788 --> 18:15.006
Girls, quiet down.

18:15.050 --> 18:16.747
- Stop laughing.
It's not funny!

18:16.791 --> 18:18.009
You're hurting her feelings.
It's--

18:18.053 --> 18:20.099
- I thought we ordered
a real cake.

18:20.142 --> 18:21.274
- We did.

18:21.317 --> 18:23.276
- It's supposed to be
her special day!

18:23.319 --> 18:25.147
Don't cry, Hailey.
I'm here.

18:25.191 --> 18:27.149
Happy's here.
Don't listen to them.

18:27.193 --> 18:29.020
♪ Happy birthday to you

18:29.064 --> 18:31.240
all: ♪ Jingle bells,
jingle bells ♪

18:31.284 --> 18:32.241
♪ Jingle all the way

18:32.285 --> 18:33.721
- Stop it!
Stop it!

18:33.764 --> 18:35.114
- [shrieks]

18:37.246 --> 18:38.900
- Hailey!

18:45.950 --> 18:48.344
- All right, all right,
I get what's going on here.

18:48.388 --> 18:49.824
It's like one of them dreams

18:49.867 --> 18:51.260
where you've got a hard-on
and no pants.

18:51.304 --> 18:52.435
[snorts]

18:52.479 --> 18:53.349
[camera shutter clicks]
- Oh, my god.

18:53.393 --> 18:54.916
Oh, work it, baby.

18:54.959 --> 18:56.004
Work it!

19:04.186 --> 19:07.146
[ethereal music]

19:07.189 --> 19:14.196
♪

19:17.504 --> 19:20.202
- [high-pitched voice]
That's fantastic.

19:21.160 --> 19:23.814
- It's so beautiful.

19:27.949 --> 19:29.907
[gasps]
Is this heaven?

19:32.214 --> 19:35.174
[ethereal music continues]

19:35.217 --> 19:42.224
♪

19:54.454 --> 19:58.240
Holy shit.

19:58.284 --> 19:59.850
- Nick.

19:59.894 --> 20:01.417
- Wow.

20:01.461 --> 20:02.810
- I'm up here.

20:06.117 --> 20:08.250
- Amanda, are we dead?

20:08.294 --> 20:10.121
[both laugh]

20:10.165 --> 20:11.384
- No, dummy.

20:11.427 --> 20:14.038
You're not getting
off the hook that easy.

20:14.082 --> 20:15.257
Neither of us is.

20:15.301 --> 20:16.389
- Then what?

20:16.432 --> 20:17.564
[both giggle]

20:17.607 --> 20:19.957
- I don't know
if you've noticed,

20:20.001 --> 20:24.005
but Mama's been
a little...off lately.

20:24.048 --> 20:25.963
Hmm.

20:26.007 --> 20:28.923
- Yeah, I just thought
it was stress.

20:28.966 --> 20:30.533
- No, you know better.

20:30.577 --> 20:32.448
You've been an addict
for ten years

20:32.492 --> 20:34.233
and a cop for ten before that.

20:34.276 --> 20:36.191
You know withdrawal
when you see it.

20:36.235 --> 20:38.149
It's in the eyes...

20:39.499 --> 20:43.807
That jonesing for something
you can't have.

20:43.851 --> 20:44.982
- [whispers]
Something so bad.

20:45.026 --> 20:46.419
- But so good.

20:46.462 --> 20:48.464
- Oh.

20:55.341 --> 20:57.517
- Hmm.

20:57.560 --> 21:00.302
- Amanda, I can't.
I made a promise

21:00.346 --> 21:01.825
to you for Hailey.

21:01.869 --> 21:03.305
No more drugs.
No more booze.

21:03.349 --> 21:05.568
- Doesn't seem fair,
does it,

21:05.612 --> 21:09.311
that to be a dad, you have
to be someone you're not?

21:09.355 --> 21:12.183
Is that what Hailey
really needs,

21:12.227 --> 21:16.231
some kind of jive counterfeit
construct of a man?

21:16.275 --> 21:18.320
- I ain't trying to be jive.
I'm trying to be good.

21:18.364 --> 21:19.930
- Shh.

21:19.974 --> 21:22.237
You can never be that.

21:22.281 --> 21:26.023
Maybe you could fake it
for a while and not very well,

21:26.067 --> 21:31.202
but what you can be
is that ass-kicking

21:31.246 --> 21:35.381
pimp daddy of destruction
you were bornto be.

21:35.424 --> 21:37.034
[gunshots]

21:37.078 --> 21:38.340
[men grunting]

21:38.384 --> 21:39.428
[chainsaw whirring]

21:39.472 --> 21:40.647
- [screaming]

21:40.690 --> 21:42.388
- Say "ah."
- Argh.

21:42.431 --> 21:44.346
- There you go.
Give in, baby.

21:44.390 --> 21:46.087
You know neither one of us
can face

21:46.130 --> 21:47.523
what we're about to face
straight.

21:47.567 --> 21:50.352
[water splashing,
people chattering indistinctly]

21:50.396 --> 21:51.919
- Is that man okay?

21:51.962 --> 21:54.269
- He's fine.
Just don't make eye contact.

21:56.489 --> 21:58.055
[knock on door]

21:58.099 --> 22:00.362
- Sockatoo? Five minutes!

22:00.406 --> 22:02.582
- Uh, all right...

22:02.625 --> 22:05.019
Ma'am.

22:05.062 --> 22:07.630
[sighs]

22:07.674 --> 22:08.936
I miss it,

22:08.979 --> 22:13.897
backstage, the dressing rooms,
the crudités,

22:13.941 --> 22:17.379
the bottles of water.

22:17.423 --> 22:20.251
[sighs]

22:20.295 --> 22:23.211
Where can a guy pinch a loaf
around here?

22:24.473 --> 22:27.346
Oh, thanks.

22:32.438 --> 22:34.396
[upbeat music]

22:34.440 --> 22:38.400
- ♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh, Sonny

22:38.444 --> 22:39.532
♪

22:39.575 --> 22:42.709
♪ Ooh-ooh, Sonny Shine

22:42.752 --> 22:47.235
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh, Sonny

22:47.278 --> 22:51.152
♪

22:51.195 --> 22:55.330
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh, Sonny

22:55.374 --> 22:57.071
♪
♪ Ooh-ooh

22:57.114 --> 22:59.465
- [screams]

22:59.508 --> 23:01.336
- ♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh, Sonny

23:01.380 --> 23:04.339
[ominous music]

23:04.383 --> 23:11.390
♪

23:16.482 --> 23:17.613
- [gasps]

23:23.619 --> 23:25.273
- [sniffing]

23:26.666 --> 23:28.363
- Sockatoo, there you are.

23:28.407 --> 23:30.147
They're calling for you
back in rehearsal.

23:30.191 --> 23:31.322
- [sniffs]

23:31.366 --> 23:32.498
- [gasps]

23:36.502 --> 23:39.026
- My therapist told me
a great way

23:39.069 --> 23:41.071
to let go of some
of my anger would be

23:41.115 --> 23:43.465
to write letters
to people I hate

23:43.509 --> 23:45.162
and then burn them.

23:45.206 --> 23:46.599
I tried it.

23:46.642 --> 23:48.514
Felt a lot better.

23:48.557 --> 23:50.646
Next time, maybe
I'll burn the letters too.

23:50.690 --> 23:53.344
- [clapping slowly]

23:53.388 --> 23:55.738
That joke was old
when you were young.

23:55.782 --> 23:57.653
Also...

23:57.697 --> 23:59.481
dinosaurs.

23:59.525 --> 24:02.745
- Well, well, well,

24:02.789 --> 24:04.617
if it isn't Sonny Snake.

24:04.660 --> 24:06.662
- Seeing you on that stage
just reminds me

24:06.706 --> 24:11.101
how unsexy all of this was
before I came along.

24:11.145 --> 24:14.061
- This is my stage, Sonny!

24:14.104 --> 24:17.064
[dramatic music]

24:17.107 --> 24:22.635
♪

24:22.678 --> 24:25.638
[ominous music]

24:25.681 --> 24:27.378
♪

24:27.422 --> 24:30.381
[spirited music]

24:30.425 --> 24:34.516
♪

24:34.560 --> 24:37.519
[sinister music]

24:37.563 --> 24:43.699
♪

24:43.743 --> 24:45.614
- Doug, what are you doing?

24:45.658 --> 24:49.662
- You made a muytragic mistake
coming here, Doug.

24:49.705 --> 24:51.533
You should have stayed
where I put you,

24:51.577 --> 24:53.187
running shtick
for schnitzel.

24:53.230 --> 24:55.406
- Oh, you'd like that,
wouldn't you?

24:55.450 --> 24:57.147
Then you wouldn't have
to look into the face

24:57.191 --> 24:58.540
of the man you betrayed.

24:58.584 --> 25:00.847
- Please,
you were washed up.

25:00.890 --> 25:02.631
Nobody was buying
Dayglo Doug anymore.

25:02.675 --> 25:06.635
They wanted something
new and dangerous and hot.

25:06.679 --> 25:08.550
- I made you.

25:08.594 --> 25:10.726
- If you had
invented Sonny Shine,

25:10.770 --> 25:12.641
you would have
invented Sonny Shine.

25:12.685 --> 25:15.426
I'll have to ruin
what's left of you, you know.

25:15.470 --> 25:16.602
I'll release your tape.

25:16.645 --> 25:18.125
I mean, you're not
too scrambled upstairs

25:18.168 --> 25:20.083
to remember our little
video party, are you?

25:20.127 --> 25:21.868
- I remember you set me up,

25:21.911 --> 25:24.784
got me all wizzle-wozzle
on airplane glue and then--

25:24.827 --> 25:27.569
- Captured the all-too-human
side of Dayglo Doug,

25:27.613 --> 25:30.093
up close and in the raw.

25:30.137 --> 25:33.270
The six fans you have left
will be heartbroken.

25:33.314 --> 25:35.577
- Well, that's going to be
a little difficult,

25:35.621 --> 25:37.231
isn't it,

25:37.274 --> 25:39.407
without this?

25:39.450 --> 25:43.585
- What's that, Doug?

25:43.629 --> 25:46.675
- Just what you used
to keep me down for 20 years.

25:48.721 --> 25:51.462
- I'm just curious.
Where'd you get that?

25:51.506 --> 25:52.507
- [laughs]

25:52.551 --> 25:54.596
- Wouldn't you love to know?

25:54.640 --> 25:57.599
The important thing is,
you've got nothing on me now,

25:57.643 --> 26:00.863
so I'll be taking back
everything you stole from me:

26:00.907 --> 26:03.170
my routine, my show.

26:03.213 --> 26:06.260
It's never too late
for a third act, Sonny,

26:06.303 --> 26:09.872
and this is mine!

26:11.744 --> 26:12.962
- [sighs]

26:13.006 --> 26:16.836
Well, Doug, you caught me
on a really bad day.

26:16.879 --> 26:21.188
Yeah, myact,
myshow

26:21.231 --> 26:24.321
is a multibillion dollar
enterprise,

26:24.365 --> 26:26.933
and the little special I have
coming up in less than 72 hours

26:26.976 --> 26:29.762
is set to turn
that B into a T-R,

26:29.805 --> 26:32.199
so my patience
is lambskin-thin.

26:32.242 --> 26:34.375
I'm under craystress.

26:34.418 --> 26:36.203
- I'll tell all, Sonny.

26:36.246 --> 26:39.902
I will sing like the loudest
canary you ever heard.

26:39.946 --> 26:43.427
- You smell...

26:43.471 --> 26:44.864
old.

26:47.388 --> 26:50.652
Doug, your act is shit.

26:50.696 --> 26:53.437
It was always shit.

26:53.481 --> 26:54.656
You can have it.

26:54.700 --> 26:58.399
But there's one thing
of yours, though,

26:58.442 --> 27:02.446
one thing I've always loved.

27:10.498 --> 27:12.282
Is this thing on?

27:12.326 --> 27:14.371
[feedback squeals]

27:14.415 --> 27:17.374
[intense music]

27:17.418 --> 27:24.425
♪

27:30.823 --> 27:32.738
[feedback squeals]

27:35.262 --> 27:38.744
[breathing heavily]

27:48.449 --> 27:51.321
[funky music]

27:51.365 --> 27:55.848
♪

27:55.891 --> 27:56.849
- Happy?

27:56.892 --> 27:58.720
- Do I look happy?

28:00.026 --> 28:01.549
- All right, all right, hey,

28:01.592 --> 28:03.594
I got something
that's gonna cheer you up.

28:04.900 --> 28:07.816
Somebody remembered
Hailey's birthday.

28:07.860 --> 28:09.383
That's right: Me.

28:09.426 --> 28:11.385
Yeah, and I'm going
right up there,

28:11.428 --> 28:13.256
and I'm gonna
get her a present.

28:13.300 --> 28:14.562
What do you think about that?

28:14.605 --> 28:17.652
- The question is,
what do you think about it?

28:17.696 --> 28:20.220
I think it's pretty obvious
I'm part of some lame attempt

28:20.263 --> 28:22.788
at working through your issues
through a series of...

28:22.831 --> 28:24.877
[grunts]

28:24.920 --> 28:27.009
Metaphorical hallucinations.

28:27.053 --> 28:28.271
- Really?

28:28.315 --> 28:29.969
- Yep, the real Happy
is knocking one back

28:30.012 --> 28:31.710
at a bar somewhere,
for all I know.

28:31.753 --> 28:33.233
We're on our own, Nick.

28:33.276 --> 28:35.409
TBH, I don't think this little
trip down the rabbit hole

28:35.452 --> 28:36.584
is gonna end well for you.

28:36.627 --> 28:38.412
- Well, who asked you,
anyway?

28:38.455 --> 28:39.935
You know, I'm done
taking parenting pointers

28:39.979 --> 28:42.503
from a flying horse.

28:42.546 --> 28:45.462
You ain't told me one thing
about Hailey that's panned out.

28:45.506 --> 28:46.899
- It's true.

28:46.942 --> 28:48.422
I guess I haven't given you
the best advice, Nick.

28:48.465 --> 28:50.293
Hailey's grown out
of the things we used to like,

28:50.337 --> 28:52.426
and maybe I don't know her
as well as I used to.

28:52.469 --> 28:55.037
- Maybe not,
so if you'll excuse me.

28:55.081 --> 28:56.778
- But I do have
one suggestion.

28:56.822 --> 28:58.345
- Yeah?

28:58.388 --> 29:00.477
- You want to give Hailey the
best gift any dad ever could?

29:00.521 --> 29:03.611
- Of course I do.
I know exactly what it is:

29:03.654 --> 29:06.570
the, um, little fluffy the
stuffed what do you call it?

29:06.614 --> 29:07.876
- No, Nick,

29:07.920 --> 29:11.575
the best gift you can give her
is to disappear.

29:11.619 --> 29:12.925
- What the hell
did you just say to me?

29:12.968 --> 29:14.578
- You bring pain
and destruction

29:14.622 --> 29:15.928
to every life you touch, Nick.

29:15.971 --> 29:17.277
- I saved her life!

29:17.320 --> 29:18.800
- You did.
Now save it again.

29:18.844 --> 29:21.063
Leave town and never look back.

29:21.107 --> 29:22.804
Ever westward, remember?

29:22.848 --> 29:24.588
- Ever westward?

29:24.632 --> 29:28.462
I'll send you ever westward
to the glue factory, you--

29:28.505 --> 29:30.638
I can be different.

29:30.681 --> 29:31.813
I can change.

29:31.857 --> 29:34.555
- The new you
is imaginary, Nick, not real.

29:34.598 --> 29:36.949
Trust me, I know
a thing or two about that.

29:36.992 --> 29:38.689
- You're supposed to be
my goddamn cheerleader!

29:38.733 --> 29:39.952
What the hell's
gotten into you?

29:39.995 --> 29:41.823
- Hailey's not the only one
growing up, Nick.

29:41.867 --> 29:43.912
Maybe I'm just seeing things
the way they really are

29:43.956 --> 29:45.435
like you always wanted me to.

29:45.479 --> 29:46.741
- Christ in a shithouse,

29:46.785 --> 29:48.351
this day just keeps getting
worse and worse.

29:48.395 --> 29:50.832
Well...great talk, Hap.

29:50.876 --> 29:52.007
Thanks a million.

29:52.051 --> 29:54.488
Pain and destruction,
TBH.

29:54.531 --> 29:55.968
Well, I know a thing or two.

29:56.011 --> 29:58.448
I'll--I'll--I'll shove a thing
or two right up your--

29:58.492 --> 29:59.536
[mutters]

29:59.580 --> 30:01.451
What are you lookin' at?

30:10.504 --> 30:12.027
- What does it all mean?

30:12.071 --> 30:13.550
What's my purpose?

30:13.594 --> 30:15.988
Life was so much simpler
when it was just me and Hailey.

30:16.031 --> 30:17.337
- I feel ya, buddy.

30:17.380 --> 30:19.905
I wouldn't wish your current
assignment on any IF.

30:19.948 --> 30:21.776
- It's not just that Nick
is a grown-up.

30:21.820 --> 30:23.691
It's not even that
he's a batshit degenerate.

30:23.734 --> 30:26.346
It's just,
does he really need me?

30:26.389 --> 30:27.434
Does anyone?

30:27.477 --> 30:28.609
- He does.

30:28.652 --> 30:30.741
- Come on, Twigs,
I'm being super serious.

30:30.785 --> 30:32.091
I feel like the whole world
is changing,

30:32.134 --> 30:33.657
leaving me behind.

30:33.701 --> 30:35.572
- From the lady.

30:41.013 --> 30:43.145
- Dude, there's your purpose
right there.

30:43.189 --> 30:44.538
Go talk to her.

30:44.581 --> 30:46.018
- I'm not in the mood.

30:46.061 --> 30:48.716
- Bo Peep buys you a drink,
you better get in the mood.

30:48.759 --> 30:51.675
- [sighs]

30:52.981 --> 30:54.853
[bar squeaks]

30:55.854 --> 30:58.900
- Uh, hi, Peep.
Thanks for the drink.

30:58.944 --> 30:59.901
[burps]

30:59.945 --> 31:02.382
Oh, maybe
I've had too much.

31:02.425 --> 31:04.166
- Hey, hot stuff.

31:04.210 --> 31:06.038
- Uh, me?

31:06.081 --> 31:07.866
- I ain't talkin'
about him,

31:07.909 --> 31:10.564
unless someone's got a match.

31:10.607 --> 31:12.609
- You look really skinny.

31:12.653 --> 31:15.961
- Ha, yeah, well, bright side:
now I can drink.

31:16.004 --> 31:17.179
Cheers.

31:17.223 --> 31:20.443
[heavy thudding]

31:30.018 --> 31:33.587
- You're cheating on me
with a heckin' horse?

31:33.630 --> 31:35.937
- Hey, there's no call
for that kind of--

31:35.981 --> 31:38.461
- You don't own me,
you psycho.

31:38.505 --> 31:40.072
We went on one date.

31:40.115 --> 31:42.465
Biggest mistake of my life.

31:42.509 --> 31:43.858
- And I don't cheat.

31:43.902 --> 31:44.990
Cheating's for cheaters.

31:45.033 --> 31:47.514
- No one's talkin' to you,
pony boy,

31:47.557 --> 31:49.081
and that was no date, Peep.

31:49.124 --> 31:54.042
What we had was sweet
roly-poly baby fat magic.

31:54.086 --> 31:55.174
- Oh, well,
then I'm just gonna leave

31:55.217 --> 31:57.045
before someone
gives me cancer.

31:57.089 --> 31:59.178
